# Implementation Plan (Archived) — TikTokio Modernization

This document outlines the final technical changes implemented to modernize the application and prepare it for Google Play Store submission.

## ✅ Completed Objectives

### 1. Core Functionality & Stability
- [x] **Video Download API**: Integrated a high-performance RapidAPI endpoint for reliable watermark-free downloads.
- [x] **External Playback**: Replaced internal players with Android System Intents for better performance and format support.
- [x] **SDK Optimization**: Upgraded `compileSdk` and `targetSdk` to API 35 (Android 15) to meet latest Play Store requirements.

### 2. Branding (Final Reverted State)
- [x] **Package ID**: Finalized as `com.tiktokionet.myapp` to maintain client compatibility.
- [x] **App Identity**: Set to **TTDownloader - TikTokio** for strong brand recognition.
- [x] **Visual Assets**: Updated launcher icons and splash screens with refined logo assets.

### 3. Build & Security
- [x] **Release Signing**: Configured `key.properties` and `build.gradle.kts` for secure release signing using a JKS keystore.
- [x] **Optimization**: Enabled ProGuard (R8) minification and resource shrinking with custom rules for the finalized package name.

---

## 🛠️ Maintenance & Verification

### Code Integrity
- All native Kotlin components reside in `android/app/src/main/kotlin/com/tiktokionet/myapp/`.
- Flutter-side logic uses Riverpod for robust state management.

### Build Verification
- Command: `flutter build appbundle --release`
- Output: `build/app/outputs/bundle/release/app-release.aab`

---
*Note: This plan has been executed and verified.*
